Customer List

The customer list screen helps users create and manage their customers. This function allows the user to capture all relevant customer information, including basic, communication, membership, professional, family, address, referrals and customer preferences.

 

Filter Selection

Unified Customer List filters are designed to narrow down the search result to get more specific data.Users can select any single filter, or can select all of them to get the desired result.

 

List Search Filters:

Search By Customer code, Customer Name, Mobile No., Email Id: The user needs to give the suggestive search wherein based on the characters entered, the dropdown will be displayed with Matching values.This will be a common search for the mentioned Parameters. 

Customer Circle: The user can select a single or multiple Customer Circle from the drop down list to get all products related to that brand.

Customer Type: All product types which have been defined should be visible here. The user can select a single or multiple type.

Customer Group: This will be a selective field with checkboxes that will show the customer group values. And on selecting any one of the check box customers having the same customer group will be displayed in the list.

Customer Country: This will be a selective field with checkboxes. This field will display the customer residence country which was selected during the customer creation.. And on selecting any one of the check box customers having the same customer country will be displayed in the list.

Customer City: This will be a selective field with checkboxes. This field will represent the city belonging to the customer. And on selecting any one of the check box customers having the same customer city will be displayed in the list.

Status: This field will have the values selected during the customer creation. And on selecting any one of the check box customers having the same status will be displayed in the list.

Age Group: This field will display the age group to which customers belong. And on selecting any one of the check box customers having the same age group will be displayed in the list.

Gender: Customer gender will be displayed in this field. And on selecting any one of the check box customers having the same gender will be displayed in the list.

Marketing Preference:  This field will display the customer to which customers have selected the same marketing preference. Once a user selects any of the options then customers having that marketing preference should get populated on the list screen.

Anniversaries between: This field will display the anniversary date range. The Customer Records will be filtered on the basis of the Anniversaries date in the given range.

Date of Birth: This field will display the date of birth date range. The Customer Records will be filtered on the basis of the date of birth  in the given range

Apply: On click of apply filters will be applied and records will be populated on screen as per selected filters.

Clear: On click of this button all selected filters will be removed.

Save Filter: On click of this option a popup will be visible on screen to name the filter  also there will be an option in popup to set filter as default so that whenever user logs in if set as default is enabled then the list screen will have records in the grid as per default filter.

Customer List Display

A customer list display is a feature that allows businesses to view and manage a list of their customers in a central location. 

Name - First name & Last name will be displayed. 

Customer Code: This will be a unique code generated for each and every customer created.

Customer Circle - This field will display a CRM Circle name against which a customer is created.

Age group -  This field will display the age group to which customers belong.

Gender - Customer gender will be displayed in this field.

Customer group -  This field will display the customer group which was defined during customer creation.

Customer Type  - This field will display the customer type which was selected during customer creation.

Country - This field will display the customer residence country which was selected during the customer creation.

 

City - This field will represent the city belonging to the customer.

Customer Status - This field will have below values: Lead, Active, Draft, Block, Delist

Source - This field will display the source where customer was created such as store / channel / HO

For Store it will display the store name.

For the channel it will display the channel name.

For HO it will display HO in this field.

Export: This button will export the records in a file in the user's local system.

 

Customers List record - Options

These fields will be available  against each Customer List record/Cards. The user will need to click on the 3 dots of each customer record to view the options.

Edit:  This option will allow the User to update / revise the Customer data. The Customer Master screen will open up with the Saved Data Values populated.

In edit mode if a user wishes to change mobile no & email id then otp verification process to be done on click of save, OTP to be sent to new mobile no & email id. Post verification new mobile no & email id to be updated as primary record.

In edit mode below fields will not be editable:

  1. Customer Type
  2. Customer Template.
  3. CRM Circle

View: To view customer details, users will have to click on the customer record row available in the list screen and the user will be redirected to customer creation UI with all fields in disabled status.

Buying History: This option will open up the new screen of Buying History details for the Customer.

Clienteling: This option will open up the new screen of Clienteling data for the Customer.

Delist: The user can click on the delist option to Delist the customer. Using this option users can delist the customer from the system.

For the Delist Customers, the following details will be anonymised  -

First, Middle & Last Name.

Email ID and Mobile No.

Gender & Title

Customer Photo.

Delisted customers will appear on the list screen with First Name as Anonymous.

The Delisted Customer Name would appear as Anonymous if his older billing transactions are Reprinted.

On click of this option the user will get a popup message with 2 actions on screen.

Message: Delisting customer will anonymise customer data and it will not allow any future billing transactions for this customer.

Action: Yes or No

On click of Yes customer data will be anonymised and customers will be delisted.

On click of No user will remain on list screen and no changes in customer record will be done.

Note -Transaction level KPIs should consider the transactions under customer ID.

  1. System will not allow users to change status to delist if there are any open orders for customers.
  2. Once a customer is Delisted, he/she cannot be enlisted again with the same customer ID. New customer have to be created manually. Also billing transactions cannot be performed for that customer
  3. In case of delisted customer edit / block options will not be visible.

Block: If the user clicks on the Block option. The User Clicks on the Block option available against a particular Customer then the Pop-up Box will appear.

The User Blocking the Customer will have to select Reason from the dropdown and define Remarks  for Blocking the Customer (Mandatory).

NOTE - 

- If the Customer is Blocked then all the Loyalty Points, GV, Credit Notes etc. will also be in Inactive state (Unavailable for use) until the Customer is Unblocked.

- If a particular user accessing the Customer Creation screen is not given the User Right of Customer Details - Create/Edit - Block Customer then the User won't be allowed to Block the Customer.

- Blocked option will be available only for Active status customers.

Unblock: The user will click on the Unblock option. This option will be only available against the customer which is blocked. Once, the User Clicks on the Unblock option available against a Customer then the customer will be unblocked for billing.

 

New Customer Creation 

The user needs to click on a single customer creation option from the plus button to create the customer here on the customer list screen. Customer creation screen will be dynamic based on the selected customer template.

If customer template Individual is selected as customer template in customer creation and as per field configuration we hide communication preference, address details, professional details, family details, referral details, customer preference & custom details all fields then in customer creation screen these tabs will not be visible.

Basic Details

Total Purchase: This field will be available beside the profile picture and it will display the Total no. of Billing/Invoicing Transactions for a given customer. This field will only be visible when any already created customer is edited from the Customer List Screen.

NPV: This field will be available beside the profile picture and it will display the Grand Total Value of the NET amount for all the invoices/transactions done till date for the Customer. This field will only be visible when any already created customer is edited from the Customer List Screen.

Status: This field will display the pre-defined status selected in the customer template. Once a customer template is selected, defined status will be populated in this field.

Profile Picture: The user will be able to upload an image from the Local System. The Picture uploaded will be automatically resized into the dimension 400 X 400 px.

Customer Type: The user will be able to define from the following options which will be displayed as Individual, Family, Employee, Corporate, Walk-In. 

Customer Template: The user will be able to select the pre-defined customer template from this field. Based on the Customer Type Selection; its respective Customer Template will be loaded as options for selection under Customer Template.

Customer Circle: The user will be able to select from the dropdown field which will have Customer Circle Name for Group & company as values users will be able to select the Customer Circle in this field while creating a customer from the CRM module. 

Customer Group: The user will be able to select the Customer Group from the dropdown. This field will also show values as per the Customer Template selection which has predefined value.

Title: The User will be able to define the Titles from dropdown & all available titles will be displayed in the drop-down field. The titles will have the following predefined option: Mr., Mrs., Master, Miss, Ms.

Customer First Name, Middle Name and Last Name: The User will be able to enter the names of the customer in these fields. All alphanumeric as well as special characters will be accepted in the three fields. The Name should be segregated in terms of First Name, Middle Name and Last Name.

Mobile No: The user will be able to select the Country code as per the country of the store. The User has to input a valid 10 digit Mobile No. This will be a Mandatory or non mandatory field based on CRM Circle for Customer Registration.

Email ID: The user will be able to input the valid email address in this field. This will be a Mandatory or non mandatory field based on CRM Circle for Customer Registration.

Gender: The user will be able to select from four options from the Dropdown of Gender- Male, Female, Unisex, Other. The options will be populated from the set-up table of Gender.

Landline No. & Secondary Mobile Number: The user will be able to input the Landline No. and also input the Secondary/Alternate Mobile Number in this field. These Fields are depended on customer template and the User can enter an alternate Telephone/Mobile No. here.

Date of Birth: The user can define the DOB with Calendar date selector. This field is  dependent on the customer template wherein the user will update the Birth Date of the Customer.

Age Group: This is a dropdown field which will populated the defined age group from age group definition. Age groups should auto-populate based on entered Date of Birth. But in case the date of birth is non-mandatory & not entered or the field itself not shown on the screen as defined in the template, then user need to select the age group as a manual entry field.

Marital Status: The User needs to select the Marital Status as the following three options will be available for selection here Single, Married, Other.

Wedding Anniversary: If the User chooses the Option 1 - Married in the Marital Status Input then this field will be available for input. Else this field will be disabled for input. The field will have the Date picker with Date,  month & Year selection. 

Country of Residence: The user will be able to select the Country of Residence of the customer from the dropdown . This field will be dependent on the customer template.

Nationality: The user will be able to select the Nationality of the customer from the dropdown . This field will be dependent on the customer template.

Passport No.: The user can enter the passport number of the customer which will be alphanumeric. This field will be dependent on the customer template.

Primary Customer Number: This will be a Search Lookup Field wherein all the List of Customers will be displayed for a single select. The search will work for customer number, First Name, Last Name. Also the suggestions displayed in the list will show customer number, First Name, Last Name. E.g. For a New Customer Named - Ganesh (with LP Balance 20); the Primary Customer was selected as - Gauri. Gauri already has 30 LP Balance. Now that she has been tagged as Primary Customer for Ganesh; the LP Balance of Gauri will increase to (30+20) = 50 LP Balance. Gauri will be able to utilize/redeem 50 LP Balance now. Ganesh will be able to utilize/redeem his 20 LP Balance out of it.

Common Tags: The user can use this field for Tagging the Customer with Several keywords so that it can be used for quick search and other purposes. When a user starts typing in this field, the related common tags will appear in the suggestions list. Users have to pick any of the tags from the list to attach it to the customer.

My Tags: The user can use this field to define and attach his own tags to the customer on the fly. Multiple Words will fit in this input field & multiple tags can be attached to a customer. After a word is typed and the user can hit the enter button, the typed word will turn into a tag. 

Heard About us From: The user can select from the multiple options from the dropdown.

 

Membership Details:

Membership Type: The user can select the Membership Type from the dropdown as Own, Affliation.

Membership Plan: The user can select the membership plan from the dropdown.

Membership ID: The User will Manually enter the Membership ID /Card No. Details here of the Customer or can also scan a barcode on the membership card to get membership ID in the field.

Tier: The User manually enters / shows  the  current tier of the customer in the program.

Membership Status: This field will show the status of the Membership Program whether it is active or inactive.

Delete & Edit Button: The user can Delete & Edit the membership record. The delete icon will be present for Affiliation Programs. When clicked on delete, the record will be removed from the screen. The edit pencil icon will also be present on the record that will bring the record again in the creation fields where data can be changed for the record.

 

Communication Preferences

Marketing  Communications: The User can either select Interested or Non-Interested. It is exclusively for marketing communications other than offers & promotions. 

Offers & Promotional Communication: The User can either select Interested or Non-Interested. It is exclusively for offers & promotions regarding communications.

Communication Mode Preferred: This field will only get enabled when the user selects the Interested in Marketing Communications or Offers & Promotional Communications.The options that will be available in the Checkboxes Buttons along with its respective Codes are Mailing Address,  Email, SMS, Social Media, WhatsApp. The user can select as per communication preference.

Mailing Address: This will be all non mandatory fields. (Although it is mandatory to fill Address Line 1, City, State, Country & Pincode, in case Mailing Address is selected for communication preferences). The fields will be

  1. Address Line 1
  2. Address Line 2
  3. Address Line 3
  4. Area
  5. Pincode (Numeric Input Only)

City: The user will be able to select the city. Once, the State is selected; all the respective Cities from the selected State Only will be displayed as options.

State: The user will be able to select the state. Once, the Country is selected; all the respective States from the selected Country Only will be displayed as options. 

Country:  By default, the Country that will be selected here for Shipping and Billing will be the one that is selected as Nationality. The User can update the same as well.

NOTE - Once the City is selected, the relevant State and Country as per the City selected will be loaded in the dropdown by default.

 

Address Details

Add Shipping Address & Add Invoicing Address: The buttons will appear on the address details screen when opened. Users can click on the button to add the Invoicing address detail. When clicked on the button the address fields will populate below with the selected address type appearing at the header. Upon adding an address on the screen the buttons will again populate at the bottom to further add any Shipping Addresses

Same as Invoicing Address - Button: This Button will only be available for the 1st Shipping Address Set. After clicking on Add Shipping Address again, this button wont be available in this 2nd address field & will nor appear in any further addresses.

Address Fields: The user will be able to input the address field. These will be the address fields appearing in every address to capture the corresponding address details. The functionality of these fields will be similar to those mentioned in the mailing address of the communication preferences section. Address Line 1, Address Line 2, Address Line 3, Area, City, State, Country, Pin/Zip Code. For every added address following fields are mandatory to fill by user- Address Line 1, City, State, Country, Pin/Zip Code.

Make it as default Address: The user will be able to click on this checkbox to define that the address will be used as a default address during any transaction of the customer.

Close Button: The user will be able to click on the close button the address card & address data entered in the fields will get removed.

 

Professional Details

Profession: The user will be able to select the profession field from the dropdown. The option will be Self Employed, Service, Retired, Unemployed.

Designation: The user will be able to input the customers designation in his/her organization.

Company Name: The user will be able to input the customers Company Name.

Type of Industry: The user will be able to select the Type of Industry from the dropdown. The option available will be Retails Industry, Oil & Gas Industry.

Office Contact No.: The User will be able to input the Office Contact No. The ISO code of office contact number should auto-populate based on selected office address fields & vice-versa.

Office Area, Country, State, City: The user can input the office address in this field. The City, State & Country should show only related results in drop-down or field values based on selected options in other fields as explained in the mailing address section. i.e.If the Country is selected then only States of the Country should populate in the States drop-down & so for the City field.

Note: This field will only be enabled when profession options are selected as SelfEmployed,  Service . For Retired, Unemployed Customers this field will be disabled.

 

Family Details

Members Name, Relation, Date of Birth: This user will be able to create family members irrespective of the values selected in the earlier fields. Both the fields Members Name & Relation are mandatory to fill in order to add the family member. A customer can add up to 30 family members. Relation will be a drop-down field with options.

 

Referral Details

Referrer's Code (If Any): The user can enter the Referrers Code shared by the customer in order to verify.

Verify Button: The user can click on the Verify button to verify whether the Referrers Code is valid or not.

Referred by Customer: This will be an auto populated field with the Customer Code if it is verified.

CUSTOMER REFERRALS 

Name, Email ID , Mobile Number: The user can enter the Name, Email ID, Mobile Number as many referrals as he/she wants.

 

Customer Preferences

Preferred Store Personnel: The field captures a salesperson which is preferred by the customer across all the stores. 

Select Product Attribute: The user can select the product attribute based on which the customer/user wants to define the brand preferences. The field will display Product Segment, Product Category, Product Subcategory, Product Class, Product Subclass.

Attribute: The field will display the list of all attribute values as per the selection of above attribute type. E.g. If Selected Product Attribute - Product Category

Then options in the Attribute field could be - Bags, Watches, Shoes, Clothing, etc. Out of this, one value could be selected to define the preferred brand & its parameters from the category.

Brand: The user will be able to search & select the required BRAND name from the list.

Dimension X, Dimension Y, Dimension Z: The user will be able to select the dimensions in the field based on Attribute Type & Brand selection.

Delete Button: The user will be able to delete the record as per the preferences.

Edit Button: The user will be able to edit each record as per the preference.

 

Custom Details

List: The user will add 10 custom Fields which will be available so that the Business User can configure additional input fields.
